choices.text:
not caring at all
about what children from other countries watch or what they eat.
Téa Altechi, 17
I found this issue paper to be very interesting because it showed different views and perspectives to the meanings of globalization and the world. Even though people might think that globalization is only about economic benefits or resources, but the globalization we usually lived in is a lot deeper than most of us might think.
Not only that globalization leads to the modernization of technology, but globalization is actually a chaotic approach to link to a better realization of life, from humans to the environment.
I myself have always depended on the information from the media, but the media doesn’t always give wide and transparent information which leads me to my own conclusion. And furthermore, some information is not even reliable, and taking them as external factors will cause chaos and distortion within the society.
In my opinion, globalization doesn’t mean accepting every single religion’s belief. It means for us to have a complete and broader understanding of others as well as to global realities in terms of culture, education, economy, arts, science, and technology. Having an internal and external factors that are both related to globalization will help you reach a better conclusion to your wide scope of life and knowledge.
Ayisha Rosidah Sirajuddin, 17
BY NICHOLAS WENGER AND ISABELLE LAVOREL Internationalisation means to get introduced to new cultures, to step outside of one’s personal space
